description:
i am not on here every day, especially in spring and summer, the growing season. if i miss your message, please be patient. if you write i will answer as soon as i see your message. i'm steve burroughs, 73, former marine, teacher, artist and writer looking for a good woman to share in this paradise i'm building..
i have a ranch i'm building in oklahoma from raw wild woods. i have a great sense of humor in spite of the world as it is today. if we can't laugh at the world and ourselves maybe we take the wrong things too seriously. i love all kinds of music except the kind that says we should kill instead of love and understand. i joined the marines because that was what men did. the put their a.. on the line to fight for this country. about my art, i was blessed with the ability to see and draw things as they appear. then a lot of practice. but i never knew i could paint until my ex gave me a paint set for my birthday, and for that and three beautiful children i will always be grateful.
when i was twelve, i went to the movies with my older brother. he had been going around looking at girls and saying he wouldn't kick them out of his bed. the movies was one of those vampire things that ,as usual, feature a very well endowed lady victim, so i said,"hum, i wouldn't kick her out of my coffin." the whole theatre roared with laughter. i have to admit it felt really good to add laughter to the lives of so many at one time.
what i’m doing with my life
as i said, i'm retired and building for the future .i'm hoping to take a trip painting places like yellowstone. i want to visit montana but i am afraid i'll fall in love with it and what do i do with this place? we've been together for 12 years and shared blood, sweat and tears (all mine!). i feel guilty just thinking about sinking my shovel in other land. but after this winter, i don't think i'll be spending many winters in montana.
i’m really good at
painting and sculpture, writing short stories and poetry, shooting, loving.i love to dance. regardless of the music, i hear "out upon the dance floor cheek to cheek."
the first things people usually notice about me
first is my smile, second my laugh. after a bit of conversation they notice my wit and intelligence.
favorite books, movies, shows, music, and food
i've been reading 4-5 books a week since i was five years old. when i worked in the library in college people would ask me where to find things instead of the card catalog. yes, you actually had to read it from those cards in little drawers.
love movies. tv classics, ncis, elementary, bugs bunny, etc.
the six things i could never do without
love, companionship, love, love,brownies and coffee and love
i spend a lot of time thinking about
i spend a lot of time trying to figure ways to solve the world's problems. i guess you can tell by the news, i haven't had much luck.
on a typical friday night i am
until i find someone, right here looking. after i find you, we can work that out.
the most private thing i’m willing to admit
i don't fu*k, i make love- and it's far from casual!god has s blessed me with good health and a body that refuses to accept old age. maybe it is because i believe what he says.
you should message me if
you are female, single mother who is looking for dad, looking for lots of love and laughs, and financial security. the va screwed my kids out of their benefits so..

description:
i live in southern maryland.just moved back after living in florida for 20 years. i currently hold certifications for and am licensed as a commercial building inspector,a building plans examiner,certified general contractor,home and property inspector and epa-lead renovator.i'm also an experienced draftsman (cadd)as well as journeyman carpenter.all my licenses are current/inactive at this point and time except for the building inspector and plans examiner licenses.sorry,but other than that,my baby blues,being tall,and being extremely handsome,is about all i have to use in order to try to impress you ladies.lol guess you could say that i'm a bad boy gone good. nice,but not disgustingly nice.a southern gentleman who's a tad rough around the edges,if you will.just a simple man.(not that kind of simple)lol don't make me have to turn you over my knee,woman!lol just kidding! unless you wanted me too,that is.lol i'm originally from southern maryland, but have been in florida since about a month before hurricane andrew. most of my family is in maryland. i'm a laid back, hard working, down to earth man. i have a good sense of humor, but usually it takes me a little time to warm up to people.looking for the lady who'll make my heart fart,bladder splatter,and liver quiver.lol woohoo!! seeking an attractive,smart,one-man woman.she don't have to be perfect.just perfect to me. 
if a woman makes more money than i do or has more material "things", i have no problem with it because i am not intimidated by women of means.at the same time , if your not ,that's ok too,because im not looking for someone to take care of me.just asking for the same respect in return that i have for hard working people regardless of gender.just thought i'd throw that out there since it seems to be an issue sometimes. 
being equals is important.i don't like control freaks.and harmony needs to be achieved, or at least attempted.i'm not in to the constant fighting, and screaming at each other scene.i'm too old for that kind of garbage.what i've learned from past relationships is that its not 50/50.and that both have to give 100% for anything to work.it can't be one-sided.you can't bail during tough times, and the grass isn't always greener on the other side of the fence.problems have to be talked out between the actual couple, and not the whole village.oh,and always remember to put the toilet seat down.lol 
if you're on the rebound,please don't waste my time.i don't want to be with you while you're (sitting,standing,laying) there scheming to yourself how you're going to get back with your ex.(or back at him)or both.when it comes to dating/relationships/romance/intimacy ,i'm not into playing second fiddle. oh,and by the way ladies,i have a strong southern accent.i've had it for 50+ years now and its not going to go away.

description:
in a nutshell: 
chronologically 56, but not feeling or looking it. not hard to look at i'm told (yes i will pay you now), slim, physically fit, great sense of humor (at times twisted but never demeaning), and very intelligent. i can be very funny and love making people laugh....sometimes to the point of peeing their pants. i'm down to earth, positive, and well grounded which i think would make me a good lightning rod. i work hard and i play harder. i'm protective, but never overbearing of those who are close to me. i enjoy cooking and can cook anything. i'm just finishing building my own home recording studio and spend a lot of my spare time with music production, mixing, etc. i'm spontaneous, not impulsive. adventurous, not foolhardy. i love flying in helicopters and have been seen jumping from perfectly good airplanes for fun. i balance things out with lots of charm, optimism, honesty, and sincerity . i'm fun to be with and i know how to take care of my woman in all the right ways. by that i mean with flowers, surprises, scented oil massages, and candle lit dinners when you least expect it. but, let your mind wander. you won't be disappointed in the other areas either.

what i'm looking for: 
i'm looking for an open minded, optimistic woman with energy to spare who prefers music over television. if you're the jealous type or lacking in self esteem, we wouldn't stand much of a chance. i'll still get the door for you even if you burned your bra in the 70's. you'll have plenty of freedom and your own time if you want because i know at the end of the day, you'll be there in my arms where you belong and want to be. of course i'll need to know what's going on behind that beautiful exterior and warm friendly smile of yours, so communication is a must, even if you have to use smoke signals or send me morse code. i like someone who's not afraid to say what's on their mind, especially as to what she wants and/or expects in our relationship as my mind reading skills have diminished over the years. honesty and fidelity are a must, and an above average sense of humor is a big plus! while casual dating is ok for some, it's not at the top of my list. what i am looking for in the near term is friendship, fun, and romance with one special lady. as for the long term, a happy, lasting, monogamous relationship.

what i'm doing with my life: 
i keep busy. working, volunteering where i can either teaching computer science at the community center to the elderly or at the humane society working with companion animals. trying to write a book and have it published within the next year or so. seems like there's never a dull moment. i have too many hobbies for that to happen.

i'm really good at: 
listening, writing, photography, cooking, (note: i'm not a slow cook or a fast cook. more like a half fast cook), home repair and fixing just about any electronic device you can find in a home. making people laugh regardless of how bad their day might have been. converting negative energy into positive energy. 

the first thing people usually notice about me: 
my optimistic and positive outlook on all things. the glass is never half full. it's either overflowing or at the very least, refillable. and technically, even if the glass is only half full of water, the other half is filled with air so it's still full.

my favorite books, music, movies, and food: 
when it comes to books, i like science fiction. i tend to read a lot of technical stuff as well. for music, it's the blues. i also produce, record, and engineer music in my home studio. just getting started but it's a blast. for food, i'll eat anything but monkey brains. i tried them once but when i was trying to slice them, they popped off of my plate onto the floor and i accidentally kicked them whilst trying to reconnoiter where they'd fallen only to have them fly under the table into my friends dogs waiting mouth. turns out my friends dog loves monkey brains. seconds anyone?

the six things i could never do without: 
my family and friends
music
my four legged friends.
laughter.....lots of laughter
learning new things every day. like how to count. :)

i spend a lot of time thinking about: 
if bats, (the nocturnal, flying mammals) hang around during the day worrying about incontinence. our troops deployed overseas who would willingly give their life to defend the freedoms we enjoy here and all too often take for granted. why there is no "infomercial" channel on tv. why our education system is so archaic and messed up and how it can be fixed. how nice it would be to no longer have a profile on this web site. if the square root of 69 is 8 something.

on a typical friday night i am: 
keeping myself entertained either out in the studio or talking to amateur radio operators around the world. or just kicking it and listening to some good blues. tv is not an option.

the most private thing i’m willing to admit:
ég hef verið fórnarlamb eigin bjartsýni mína þegar það kemur að elska. do you speak icelandic?

you should message me if: 
you're wondering what it is like to be treated with respect. if the words "karma" and "destiny" are not foreign to you. if we've ever met in a previous life and you want to get reacquainted. (kidding). if music and humor are important to you. if negativity and cynicism bounce off of you like "deflecto-man". if you're positive and you're sure of it. if you want a friend who really knows what the word "friend" means. or if any of the following makes sense.

description:
welcome!
i think i am a reasonable communicator (both talking & listening), with varied interests including gardening, fitness, food, music & life! i have a great soh. (that in itself might be enough for you to want to contact me!!).
i like playing the piano (including duets) & singing (for fun), but i am fairly average at each - so if you're looking for billy joel you're in the wrong place!!
i love watching most types of movies & documentaries. moving movies move me - i do shed tears in such situations (i try to keep outright sobbing to a minimum though!!). rarely watch tv.
i also like the challenge of personal development (physically, mentally & spiritually), always learning, bushwalking, camping, listening to musical & educational cds, activities that stimulate the mind (not into trivia!!), even the odd practical joke!
tend to be practical rather than stylish. not a fashion aficionado.
i love reading - i'm a bit of a bookshop browser. some of the best books i've read have serendipitously jumped out at me from bookshop & library shelves!
travelled some & would love to travel more - prefer more out-of-the-way places than mainstream, but love either.
i'm divorced & have two daughters who i love very much. they are still a big part of my life & i relish the interactions we have! life certainly is great! but there is more to my life.
as i said - always learning!
i still work part-time - because i love it. spent my life learning - it's good to give some back.
not here because i'm lonely - au contraire! to inspire, & be inspired! - & find a partner & friend in the process - to expand my view of the world - and/or yours!!
if you've read this far - thank you. why not drop me a line? i don't bite - much. & we might just form a great friendship- or maybe more!!
i wish you well.

soy un hombre muy sincero... well, that is just about all spanish i know apart from taco, sangria, mujer and a few other appetizing things.

i prefer to live in the country or a very small town and do not like huge cities. also i am a kind of heat-seeking missile and love warm climate (as in tropical) and sunshine, so outdoors activity can be more fun. of course i like everything to do with water, boats and beaches. 
there was already more than my fair share of unwanted "drama" in my past, so i am hoping to find a truly loving and faithful woman for marriage and a happy life together and to share most things in life with. her inner values are more important than outwardly appearance, and indeed my preference is a natural look. if you want to impress me, just be yourself - i do not tell lies, and i expect to be treated likewise. as nobody can be perfect (except in god's eyes), i do not expect perfection. even angels become somewhat shop-worn as time passes on.
in case you like, what i wrote, please let me know soon. maybe the long search will be over soon...

letter to victim:
hello dear,
i am mr juan meza it gives me joy to send this mail to you. how is your day, hope cool. let me tell you more about myself. i’m god fearing, honest, caring, trustworthy and understanding. i have an easy heart which makes me enjoy helping people and i’m also into charity giving. i want to spend the rest of my life with someone who is friendly, honest, caring,trustworthy and god fearing. i have a 8yrs old son, his name is juan jr . i want a serious relationship with a honest and understanding woman because i’m not getting any younger so i don’t want to play games and i want something serious with the right woman who is willing too, that’s why i’ll put in more effort to see where god will lead us to, what do you think? i was in a relationship with another lady after i lost my wife and it was serious and leading to marriage, but i discovered she wasn’t actually in love but was after my wealth. actually its a long story.
it has been difficult all these years without a woman to love and call my own but i believe god has a reason for everything. not long ago a friend of mine advised me to go on dating site that i can meet my miss right because he met his wife about 4 years ago on confirio and that was how i registered and saw your profile and found interest in you. there is something in you that just make me feel cool when i think about you, that why i would like us to start up something because i know that there’s something so special in you that i have not yet discovered. i have not been in a relationship for long now because, i don’t enjoy the one-night stand thing, when you quickly jump into a relationship believe me, you will also jump out quickly and i don’t need that kind of thing in my life right now. i want a relationship that can lead to something great, after all if there is a chemistry between a man and a woman nothing can stand in the way. i really think it’s time to build a relationship.
i am a man who will never cheat on my partner, my demised wife can testify to that because i believe that god made one man for one woman and so i should be like that. it is very important for me to build a life of stability, security, and opportunity for the special person i hope to share my thoughts, feelings, experiences, dreams and fantasies with, and to offer the best opportunities for our children, both mine and that special person children, and that is my focus at this time and i also do enjoy my job. please do not mind my long story, i am just excited about meeting you. can you please tell me more about yourself? your family and all that, and you can also tell me your favorite food.. hope to read from you soon.
have a lovely day.
cheers & hugs,

everyone gets a fair shake until they prove otherwise. i am non-secular and won't debate religion as long as people don't try to proselytize. "spiritual" seems the closest match, since i do not belong to any organized religion but have high ethical standards. 

my myers-briggs type indicator (mbti) is intj. people of this type are generally introverted and reticent about sharing information; we also don't "get" interpersonal dynamics, so it's best to be direct and blunt. 

it is unfortunate that circumstances drastically limit pursuing a relationship where language or distance are obstacles. conversation is welcome but the above will surely limit potential opportunities to meet face-to-face, which is my primary goal from this forum. 

thank you for reading my profile, and best wishes for you and yours!
